splays\", \"from\": 238, \"to\": 255}, {\"ngram\": \"the circuit\", \"from\": 259, \"to\": 270}, {\"ngram\": \"the ultimate prize\", \"from\": 289, \"to\": 307}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She could not have known at that point that this would be her only appearance at the Olympic Games or that fate would present a surprising reward for her efforts and dedication over the years.\", \"from\": 334, \"to\": 526, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that point\", \"from\": 362, \"to\": 372}, {\"ngram\": \"her only appearance\", \"from\": 392, \"to\": 411}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 415, \"to\": 432}, {\"ngram\": \"that fate\", \"from\": 436, \"to\": 445}, {\"ngram\": \"a surprising reward\", \"from\": 460, \"to\": 479}, {\"ngram\": \"her efforts\", \"from\": 484, \"to\": 495}, {\"ngram\": \"dedication\", \"from\": 500, \"to\": 510}, {\"ngram\": \"the years\", \"from\": 516, \"to\": 525}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Carter was officially upgraded to the bronze medal position in 2023 by the International Olympic Committee following the disqualification of Natalya Antyukh from Russia, who crossed the line first in London but was later proven to be involved in the Russian doping scandal.\", \"from\": 528, \"to\": 801, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 528, \"end\": 534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Carter\", \"score\": 0.9950010684583732, \"rank\": 0.005015985002349619, \"text\": \"Carter\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Carter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Carter\"}, {\"begin\": 603, \"end\": 634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {